<html xmlns:o='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office' xmlns:w='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40'><head><meta charset='utf-8'><title>Text To Word</title></head><body><h1>üåê Judix Task App &ndash; Postman / API Documentation</h1>
<p>This document provides all the <strong>API endpoints</strong> for the Judix Task App, including request methods, headers, body, and example responses. You can use this in <strong>Postman</strong> or any API testing tool.</p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>1. User Signup</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>POST /users/signup</code><br><strong>Description:</strong> Register a new user</p>
<p><strong>Request Headers:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Content-Type: application/json
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Request Body (JSON):</strong></p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Success Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 201 Created</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "success": true,
  "token": "&lt;JWT_TOKEN&gt;",
  "user": {
    "_id": "user_id",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com"
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Error Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 400 Bad Request</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "success": false,
  "message": "User already exists"
}
</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2><strong>2. User Login</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>POST /users/login</code><br><strong>Description:</strong> Login user and issue JWT</p>
<p><strong>Request Headers:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Content-Type: application/json
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Request Body (JSON):</strong></p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Success Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 200 OK</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "success": true,
  "token": "&lt;JWT_TOKEN&gt;",
  "user": {
    "_id": "user_id",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com"
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Error Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 401 Unauthorized</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Invalid email or password"
}
</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2><strong>3. Get User Profile</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>GET /users/profile</code><br><strong>Description:</strong> Fetch logged-in user profile</p>
<p><strong>Request Headers:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer &lt;JWT_TOKEN&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Success Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 200 OK</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "_id": "user_id",
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Error Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 401 Unauthorized</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "message": "Not authorized, token failed"
}
</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2><strong>4. Update User Profile</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>PUT /users/profile</code><br><strong>Description:</strong> Update profile information</p>
<p><strong>Request Headers:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer &lt;JWT_TOKEN&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Request Body (JSON):</strong></p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "name": "John Doe Updated",
  "email": "johnupdated@example.com",
  "password": "newpassword123"
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Success Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 200 OK</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "_id": "user_id",
  "name": "John Doe Updated",
  "email": "johnupdated@example.com",
  "token": "&lt;NEW_JWT_TOKEN&gt;"
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Error Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 400 Bad Request</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "message": "User not found"
}
</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2><strong>5. Get All Tasks</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>GET /tasks</code><br><strong>Description:</strong> Fetch all tasks for the logged-in user</p>
<p><strong>Request Headers:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer &lt;JWT_TOKEN&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Success Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 200 OK</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">[
  {
    "_id": "task_id_1",
    "title": "Task 1",
    "description": "Description 1",
    "user": "user_id"
  },
  {
    "_id": "task_id_2",
    "title": "Task 2",
    "description": "Description 2",
    "user": "user_id"
  }
]
</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2><strong>6. Create Task</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>POST /tasks</code><br><strong>Description:</strong> Add a new task</p>
<p><strong>Request Headers:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer &lt;JWT_TOKEN&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Request Body (JSON):</strong></p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "title": "New Task",
  "description": "This is a new task"
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Success Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 201 Created</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "_id": "task_id",
  "title": "New Task",
  "description": "This is a new task",
  "user": "user_id"
}
</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2><strong>7. Update Task</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>PUT /tasks/:id</code><br><strong>Description:</strong> Update a specific task</p>
<p><strong>Request Headers:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer &lt;JWT_TOKEN&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Request Body (JSON):</strong></p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "title": "Updated Task Title",
  "description": "Updated description"
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Success Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 200 OK</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "_id": "task_id",
  "title": "Updated Task Title",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "user": "user_id"
}
</code></pre>
<hr>
<h2><strong>8. Delete Task</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Endpoint:</strong> <code>DELETE /tasks/:id</code><br><strong>Description:</strong> Delete a specific task</p>
<p><strong>Request Headers:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer &lt;JWT_TOKEN&gt;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Success Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 200 OK</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "message": "Task removed"
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Error Response:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> 404 Not Found</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Body:</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  "message": "Task not found"
}
</code></pre>
